            // Privacy Policy
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy1", "Privacy Policy" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy1", "Paycor, Inc. (“We,” “Our” or “Us,” as appropriate) takes the privacy of personal information you may provide Us seriously. This Privacy Policy applies to all users of the www.paycor.com website (the “Website”) and all mobile applications released by Us through the Apple App Store or the Google Play Store (the “Applications” and together with the Website, collectively, the “Products”), and applies only to information gathered via the Products, whether submitted directly by you or your previous, current or prospective employer, or by any of Our other clients on your behalf. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, you must immediately cease use of the Products." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy2", "Information collected" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy2", "We collect personal information that you voluntarily provide via the Products, when you interact with Us, sign up to receive alerts, or make a purchase (“Personal Information”).  The Personal Information collected through the Products may include some or all of the following: name, gender, user name, or contact information such as street address, phone number, email address, geolocation information, and any other information you may voluntarily provide. You have the choice whether or not to disclose Personal Information, however, some parts of the Products may be impossible to access or use if you do not disclose Personal Information. Therefore, at times, you may be requested to voluntarily supply Us with your Personal Information. Generally this information is requested when you:\n\n-   Submit an inquiry;\n-   Participate in some of the online activities We run from time to time;\n-   Subscribe to or set up an account with the Products;\n -   Purchase products or services through the Products; or\n -   Communicate with Us(via e-mail, phone, postal mail, etc.)." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy3", "Mobile Devices" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy3", "If you use a mobile device (“Device”) to access any of the Products, We may collect certain information in addition to what We collect when you use other kinds of devices (e.g., computers) to access the Products. We may receive information about your location and your mobile Device, including a unique identifier for your Device and your mobile operating system. We may, at times, use this information to provide you with location-based services and information, such as advertising, search results, and other personalized content. Most Devices provide users with the ability to disable location services.  If you have questions about how to disable your Device's location services, We recommend you contact your mobile service carrier or your Device manufacturer." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy4", "Use of Personal Information" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy4", "We may use your Personal Information for any of the following purposes:\n\n-   To understand how users use the Products.\n-   To administer or to help Us develop and improve the Products or Our offerings.\n-   To respond to specific requests from users.\n-   To protect the security or integrity of the Products.\n-   To send notices of special promotions, offers or solicitations.\n-   To conduct market research surveys.\n-   To promote and market Our business and various products.\n-   To provide you with the services you request or are otherwise offered through the Products.\n-   To enforce applicable terms of use for the Products and or this Privacy Policy, and to otherwise comply with all laws, rules and regulations.\n\nPursuant to the California Online Privacy Protection Act, neither We nor any of the Products follow the Do Not Track setting of your web browser." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy5", "Sharing of Information" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy5", "We may share Personal Information with third parties under any of the following circumstances:-\n\n-   With your previous, current or prospective employer or as instructed by your previous, current or prospective employer.\n-   In connection with a court order, subpoena, government investigation, or when otherwise required by law, rule or regulation.\n-   In the event of a corporate sale, merger, acquisition, or similar event.\n-   Working with third party companies to support the Products' operation and administration.\n-   In connection with working with third party entities to perform certain business-related functions (e.g., mailing campaigns to customers, maintaining databases, fulfilling or responding to your requests or purchases) to the extent needed for such third parties to perform their specific functions.\n-   In connection with providing aggregated anonymous information concerning member usage of the Products to third parties, such as for advertisers, for purposes that We deem appropriate for service administration. \n-   In connection with the sale of any aggregated anonymized data based on the Personal Information you provide Us. \n\nWe will not sell, rent, loan, transfer, or otherwise disclose any Personal Information to third parties except as set forth in this Privacy Policy. \nPursuant to California Civil Code Section 1798, California residents may ask companies with whom they have an established business relationship to provide information about Our sharing of Personal Information with third parties for direct marketing purposes. We do not share any California consumer Personal Information with third parties for marketing purposes without consent." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy6", "Collection of Non-Personally Identifiable Information" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy6", "We intend to continue improving the content and function of the Products. For this reason, We may monitor customer traffic patterns and service usage to help Us improve the design and layout of Our Products.  As such, in addition to Personal Information provided to Us as identified above, We may also collect certain non-personally identifiable information. For example, Our servers may automatically identify computers by their IP addresses, and We may use certain tracking technologies (such as cookies), as further described below. We and each of Our service providers may use this non-personally identifiable information to analyze trends, administer the Products, track users' movement and gather broad demographic information for aggregate use. We will not link these IP addresses to Personal Information other than to the extent necessary to enforce the Products' terms of service, including in forum environments." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy7", "Use of Cookies" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy7", "Our Products may use tracking technologies such as “cookies” to provide users with tailored information upon each return visit. Cookies are a common part of many Products that allow small text files to be sent by a Products, accepted by your web browser, and then placed on your hard drive as recognition token. Every time you visit the Products, cookies may record basic technical information, such as your domain name, the address of the last URL visited prior to the Products, your browser, and your operating system. You do not need to enable cookies to visit the Products; however, some parts of the Products will be impossible to use if cookies are disabled. Cookies do not contain any Personal Information." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy8", "Updating Personal Information" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy8", "You control the accuracy of your Personal Information. If your Personal Information changes, please correct, update or delete it by logging into your account at the Products.\n\nAfter termination of your account, We will have no obligation to maintain or provide any of your Personal Information and may thereafter, unless legally prohibited, delete all of your Personal Information in Our systems or otherwise in Our possession or under Our control. We may also retain all or a subset of your Personal Information for business or legal purposes." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy9", "Protection of Information" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy9", "While We will take reasonable security measures to protect your Personal Information, no transmission of data over the Internet can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. As a result, given the electronic nature of the Internet, by using the Products, you accept the inherent risks in doing so, including, but not limited to, the security risks of interception, unauthorized access, the risks of corruption and the risks of viruses or other harmful devices." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy10", "Third Party Links" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy10", "The Products may contain links to other applications, services or websites  that may not be owned or operated by Us. We cannot control and are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of such other applications, services or websites. We encourage you to read the privacy statements of each application that you use and website that you visit." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy11", "Social Networking Sites" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy11", "Integration with social networking sites may be present through the Products, and such integration is provided to enhance member experience. If you access the Products through your other social networking account(s), you authorize Us to collect relevant information necessary to enable the Products to access and collect your data contained within that particular social networking service (e.g., such as your Facebook profile information). Please remember, however, that the manner in which such third party social network provider uses, stores and discloses your information is governed solely by that provider's policies, and We will have no liability or responsibility for the privacy practices or other actions of any third party site or provider that you may enable and link to your online experience with Us." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy12", "Updates to this Privacy Policy" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy12", "We updated this Privacy Policy effective as of the date set forth above. It may be appropriate to update Our Privacy Policy and other terms and conditions from time to time. We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time in Our sole discretion, with or without advance notice. We will post any changes on the Privacy Policy page of the Products so users are always aware of any change. We encourage you to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed about how We are helping to protect the Personal Information We receive from you. Your continued use of the Products shall constitute your agreement to this Privacy Policy and any of its updates. If We decide to use your Personal Information in a manner not set forth in this Privacy Policy, We will notify registered account holders by e-mail to the e-mail addresses on record. If you choose to visit the Site or use any of Our other services, your visit and/or any dispute over privacy is subject to this Privacy Policy and Our Terms of Use." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy13", "Children's Privacy" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy13", "We do not knowingly collect Personal Information from anyone under 13 years old. If you are under 18 years old, you may use the Products only with the permission and involvement of your parent(s) or guardian." },
            { "titlePrivacyPolicy14", "Contact" },
            { "descPrivacyPolicy14", "If you have questions about your privacy rights, please contact your employer’s human resources department. If you have any further questions concerning this Privacy Policy or Our privacy practices, please contact Us at 800.381.0053" },

